text: From Nato headquarters Mr. Rusk went to see President de Gaulle and informed him of the Vienna outcome. Last night Mr. Rusk arrived in London in time to join the Buckingham Palace dinner and to fly home with the President. In DUEssEL DORF, Chancellor Adenauer said the Vienna talks "might be the beginning of a slight improvement, but no big changes should be expected in the political situation.
